(15, 135164, 'Independiente', 1905, 'Soccer', 'Argentinian Primera DivisiÃ³n', '4406', 'Jorge Almiron', '', '', '', 'On 4 March 1928, in a match against PeÃ±arol of Uruguay that ended in a draw, Independiente established the first stadium in South America. The stadium would later be known as Doble Visera.\r\n\r\nThe Estadio Libertadores de AmÃ©rica was closed for repairs in 2007, and reopened 28 October 2009 in a league match against ColÃ³n, which Independiente won 3â€“2. During construction, Independiente played their home games in four different fields.', 'Avellaneda', 'clubaindependiente.com', 'www.facebook.com/Independiente', 'twitter.com/Independiente', 'instagram.com/caindependiente', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/svqury1422408109.png', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/jersey/rxvqyp1423784011.png', ''),
