(117, 133890, 'FC NordsjÃ¦lland', 1991, 'Soccer', 'Danish Superliga', '4340', 'Ã“lafur KristjÃ¡nsson', '', '', '', 'Farum Park is a football stadium, located in Farum, Denmark and is the home ground of FC NordsjÃ¦lland. It has a capacity of 10,100 of which 9,800 are seated. Farum Park is the first stadium in the Danish Superliga with an artificial turf, installed in 2012. The grass is from Limonta Sport - a leading company in the production and distribution of synthetic grass for sports. Farum Park is a modern stadium with LED-banners, a hotel with 35 rooms and a fitness center.', 'IdrÃ¦tsvÃ¦nget 2 3520 Farum', 'www.fcn.dk', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/ttuwyt1422407203.png', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/jersey/qxyqxq1423795407.png', ''),
