(220, 134718, 'Creteil', 1936, 'Soccer', 'French Ligue 2', '4401', 'Philippe Hinschberger', '', '', '', 'Stade Dominique Duvauchelle is a multi-use stadium in CrÃ©teil, France. It takes its name from a local sports journalist who died shortly before the stadiums inauguration. It is currently used mostly for football matches and is the home stadium of US CrÃ©teil-Lusitanos Football. The stadium was built with an original capacity of approximately 6,000. It increased its capacity to 12,150 people in February 2006.\r\n\r\nIts record attendance for a league match was for a match between CrÃ©teil and Saint Etienne on 5 August 2001 with 6325 spectators. The record for a cup match is 8000 in a match hosted there by amateur team US Lusitanos Saint-Maur against Bordeaux in the round of 32 of the French Cup on 19 January 2002.', 'CrÃ©teil', 'www.uscl.fr', 'www.facebook.com/pages/US-CrÃ©teil-Lusitanos', 'twitter.com/uscl_football', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/vxuwpx1426869851.png', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/jersey/tqruss1423797921.png', ''),
