(222, 133705, 'Evian Thonon Gaillard', 2003, 'Soccer', 'French Ligue 2', '4401', 'Safet SuÅ¡iÄ‡', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/stadium/qsyqvv1423686243.jpg', 'Evian formerly played its home matches at the Stade Joseph-Moynat in the clubs hometown, but moved to the Parc des Sports in nearby Annecy for the 2010â€“11 season as the Joseph-Moynat did not meet the Ligue de Football Professionnels standards. The Parc des Sports will serve as a temporary stadium for the club, while the club contemplates building a new facility or renovating the Stade Joseph-Moynat. Prior to moving to its current facility, Evian sought to play at the Stade de GenÃ¨ve in nearby Geneva.\r\n\r\nThe club is owned by Groupe Danone, owner of the Evian brand of mineral water. Danones CEO Franck Riboud is honorary president of the club.', 'Annecy, France', 'www.etgfc.com', 'www.facebook.com/etgfc', 'twitter.com/etgfc', 'instagram.com/eviantgfc', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/urstyu1420397456.png', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/jersey/qwpssy1423781810.png', ''),
