(262, 133653, 'Freiburg', 1904, 'Soccer', 'German 2. Bundesliga', '4399', 'Christian Streich', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/stadium/uttyws1423712691.jpg', 'The Schwarzwald-Stadion is a football stadium in Freiburg, Baden-WÃ¼rttemberg, Germany. It is currently used mostly for football matches and is the home stadium of Sport-Club Freiburg. The stadium holds 24,000 spectators and was built in 1953. The stadium was called the Dreisamstadion until June 2004. Following that it was named the Badenova-Stadion, the Mage Solar Stadion, and for a short time the Stadion an der SchwarzwaldstraÃŸe. Due to a sponsorship deal, it is currently named the Schwarzwald-Stadion.\r\n\r\nIn 2012, modernising the stadium was deemed unprofitable. In February 2015, a hotly discussed referendum was held to determine whether a new stadium should be built and if so, where. The citizens of Freiburg who participated in the referendum voted in favour of the construction of a new stadium at the Wolfswinkel nearby Freiburgs municipal airport.', 'Freiburg im Breisgau, Baden-WÃ¼rttemberg', 'www.scfreiburg.com', 'de-de.facebook.com/SCFreiburg', 'twitter.com/sc_freiburg', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/survps1420476132.png', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/jersey/xtsxry1423782457.png', ''),
