(286, 134779, 'Mgladbach', 1900, 'Soccer', 'German Bundesliga', '4331', 'Lucien Favre', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/stadium/rtyxxp1423713572.jpg', 'Borussia-Park (German pronunciation: ; official name "Stadion im Borussia-Park") in MÃ¶nchengladbach, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany is the home stadium of German Bundesliga club Borussia MÃ¶nchengladbach. It replaced the smaller BÃ¶kelberg stadium, which no longer satisfied modern safety standards and international requirements, in July 2004.\r\n\r\nBorussia-Park has a capacity of up to 54,057, of which 16,145 are standing-room only due to popular demand. For international games, the standing room is converted into temporary seating for a total seating capacity of 46,249.\r\n\r\nThe new stadium features amenities such as VIP lounges, fanshop and sports bar, and cost 85 million euro to construct.\r\n\r\nDespite its large capacity and relative youth, the stadium missed out on holding matches during the 2006 World Cup, which Germany hosted. It was the largest capacity Bundesliga stadium to do so.', 'MÃ¶nchengladbach, Germany', 'www.borussia.de', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/yrsptp1420764101.png', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/jersey/rpspuq1423782654.png', ''),
(287, 133665, 'Mainz', 0, 'Soccer', 'German Bundesliga', '4331', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/stadium/rpvquu1423713456.jpg', '', '', 'www.mainz05.de', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/xpsqwy1420476245.png', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/jersey/vxrppp1423782409.png', ''),
(288, 133661, 'Schalke 04', 1904, 'Soccer', 'German Bundesliga', '4331', 'Roberto Di Matteo', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/stadium/rywvwq1420677493.jpg', 'Veltins-Arena (German pronunciation: ; originally Arena AufSchalke ) is a football stadium in Gelsenkirchen, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. It opened in 2001, as the new home ground for German Bundesliga club Schalke 04.\r\n\r\nIt hosted the 2004 UEFA Champions League final and 5 matches in the 2006 FIFA World Cup, including a quarter-final. It has a league capacity of 61,482 (standing and seated) and an international capacity of 53,951 (seated only). The stadium has a retractable roof and a retractable pitch. The naming rights to the stadium were sold on 1 July 2005 to the German brewery Veltins.\r\n\r\nPlans to construct a new stadium emerged in the late 1990s, as fans and managers sought to move out of the outdated Parkstadion, and create a thoroughly modern multifunctional arena. Following Schalke 04s historic 1997 victory in the UEFA Cup, and the clubs upcoming 100th anniversary in 2004, the contract to construct a â‚¬186 million stadium was given in 1998 to the German construction firm HBM.', 'Gelsenkirchen, Germany', 'www.schalke04.de', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/wwvxqr1420476341.png', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/jersey/swwqsp1423782585.png', ''),
(289, 133660, 'Stuttgart', 0, 'Soccer', 'German Bundesliga', '4331', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/stadium/wyuyrx1423712155.jpg', '', '', 'www.vfb.de', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/qyxtqp1420476373.png', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/jersey/upqtvw1423782670.png', ''),
(290, 133662, 'Werder Bremen', 1899, 'Soccer', 'German Bundesliga', '4331', 'Viktor Skripnik', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/stadium/vqwtrx1423705316.jpg', 'The Weserstadion (German pronunciation: ) is a multi-purpose stadium in Bremen, Germany. The Weserstadion is scenically situated on the north bank of the Weser River and is surrounded by lush green parks (the name Werder is a regional German word for â€œriver peninsulaâ€). The city center is only about a kilometer away. It is the home stadium of German Bundesliga club Werder Bremen.\r\n\r\nIt presented a bid to be a host city in the 2006 FIFA World Cup, which was ultimately turned down.\r\n\r\nLegendary artists that have performed at the stadium include Bon Jovi, Michael Jackson, Depeche Mode, Metallica, The Rolling Stones, Guns N Roses, Tina Turner and Van Halen, among others.\r\n\r\nThe Weser Stadium is in a current state of modification, for the most part controlled by Hauke Wilkens. The Stadium will be transformed into a pure football venue, with the purpose of tightening the atmosphere by moving the spectators closer to the pitch. Modifications therefore include the removal of the space in front of the curves with the addition of a third tier.', 'Bremen, Deutschland', 'www.werder.de', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/ussqpx1420476395.png', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/jersey/yyruxt1423782422.png', ''),
(291, 133655, 'Wolfsburg', 1945, 'Soccer', 'German Bundesliga', '4331', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/stadium/xtpxyp1423711901.jpg', 'Volkswagen Arena is a multi-purpose stadium in Wolfsburg, Lower Saxony, Germany and serves as the home stadium of the 2008â€“09 Bundesliga champions VfL Wolfsburg. The Volkswagen Arena replaced the former stadium of VfL Wolfsburg, the VFL Stadion.', 'Wolfsburg', 'www.vfl-wolfsburg.de', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/sruyxx1420476413.png', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/jersey/rvsvvx1423782520.png', ''),
(292, 133753, 'AEK', 1924, 'Soccer', 'Greek Superleague Greece', '4336', 'Gus Poyet', '', '', '', 'The Olympic Stadium of Athens "Spiros Louis" (Greek: ÎŸÎ»Ï…Î¼Ï€Î¹Î±ÎºÏŒ Î£Ï„Î¬Î´Î¹Î¿ Î‘Î¸Î·Î½ÏŽÎ½ "Î£Ï€ÏÏÎ¿Ï‚ Î›Î¿ÏÎ·Ï‚", OlympiakÃ³ StÃ¡dio "Spiros Louis") is part of the Athens Olympic Sports Complex. It is named after the first modern Olympic marathon race winner in 1896, Spiros Louis. The stadium hosts one of the biggest sport clubs in Greece, AEK Athens', 'Athens', 'www.aekfc.gr', 'www.facebook.com/AEK.FC.OFFICIAL', 'twitter.com/AEK_FC_OFFICIAL', 'instagram.com/aekfc_official', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/rpqvwx1448206238.png', '', ''),
(293, 133752, 'Asteras Tripolis', 1931, 'Soccer', 'Greek Superleague Greece', '4336', 'Staikos Vergetis', '', '', '', 'Theodoros Kolokotronis Stadium (Greek: Î“Î®Ï€ÎµÎ´Î¿ Î˜ÎµÏŒÎ´Ï‰ÏÎ¿Ï‚ ÎšÎ¿Î»Î¿ÎºÎ¿Ï„ÏÏŽÎ½Î·Ï‚), formerly known as Asteras Tripolis Stadium, is a football stadium in Tripoli, Greece. The stadium has been the home stadium of Asteras Tripoli F.C. until the construction of the New Asteras Tripolis Stadium. The stadium holds 7,616 seats. The stadium was renamed in honour of the hero of the Greek War of Independence, Theodoros Kolokotronis, on November 22, 2012.', 'Tripoli, Greece', 'www.asterastripolis.gr', 'www.facebook.com/asterastripolisfc.gr/', 'twitter.com/AsterasfcTwit', 'instagram.com/asterastripolisfc', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/stwuty1448206099.png', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/jersey/wwstpv1423796141.png', ''),
(294, 133744, 'Atromitos', 1923, 'Soccer', 'Greek Superleague Greece', '4336', 'Traianos Dellas', '', '', '', 'Peristeri Stadium (also known as the Atromitos Stadium) is a multi-purpose stadium in Peristeri, a western district of Athens, in Greece.\r\n\r\nIt is currently used mostly for football matches and is the home stadium of Atromitos.\r\n\r\nThe stadium was built in 1947 and has a seating capacity of 9,050.', 'Athens', 'www.atromitosfc.gr', 'www.facebook.com/ATROMITOS.F.C.Official', 'twitter.com/atromitos1923', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/xqryxu1448207435.png', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/jersey/xtytpt1423796282.png', '');
