'', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/xxxprq1422939486.png', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/logo/uwtvyq1422939517.png'),
(731, 135195, 'St. George Illawara Dragons', 1998, 'Rugby', 'Australian National Rugby League', '4416', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/stadium/ssvwuu1422941535.jpg', 'Jubilee Oval, also known as Kogarah Oval, is a multipurpose stadium in Carlton, Sydney, Australia. The stadium is primarily used for rugby league and is the home of National Rugby League (NRL) team St. George Illawarra Dragons. The oval has also hosted soccer matches, including hosting Sydney Olympic FC during the 2003â€“04 National Soccer League (NSL) season.\r\n\r\nThe ground hosted its first game of rugby league in March 1936 when the St. George Dragons were defeated by the Newtown Bluebags in an exhibition match. The stadium has undergone several constructions over the years and one is still being planned for the foreseeable future. The first official game was played on 22 April 1950 in which the Dragons lost 17-15 to South Sydney.', 'Sydney, Australia', '', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/qpvxqq1422941275.png', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/logo/ssvxsw1422941340.png'),
(732, 135192, 'Sydney Roosters', 1908, 'Rugby', 'Australian National Rugby League', '4416', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/stadium/uxssqv1422943686.jpg', 'Sydney Football Stadium (SFS), currently known by its sponsorship name Allianz Stadium, is a football stadium located in Moore Park, Sydney, Australia. Built in 1988, the stadium is Sydneys premier rectangular field venue for rugby league, rugby union and association football. The Kangaroos, the Wallabies and the Socceroos occasionally play at the stadium, while the Sydney Roosters, NSW Waratahs and Sydney FC are the grounds major tenants.\r\n\r\nSydney Football Stadium usually hosts both NRL semi finals and one preliminary final, and also held the annual pre-season Charity Shield football match between South Sydney and St George Illawarra for a number of years. All NSWRL / ARL Rugby League Grand Finals as well as the first Grand Final under the NRL banner were played there between 1988 and 1998.\r\n\r\nThe stadium is located next to the Sydney Cricket Ground.', 'Sydney, Australia', '', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/srwpsr1422943177.png', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/logo/rqwqvy1422943190.png'),
(733, 135189, 'Wests Tigers', 1999, 'Rugby', 'Australian National Rugby League', '4416', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/stadium/xyqpts1422989037.jpg', 'Campbelltown Stadium, formerly Orana Park and Campbelltown Sports Ground, is a multi-use stadium in Leumeah, New South Wales, Australia, owned by Campbelltown City Council. It is the full-time home ground for the Western Suburbs Magpies District Rugby League Football Club and is one of three home grounds for the Wests Tigers Rugby League Football Club. The stadium has a nominal capacity of 20,000, with a recorded highest crowd figure of 20,527 for a game between Wests Tigers and North Queensland Cowboys in NRL season 2005. It is located adjacent to Leumeah railway station.', ' 	Pembroke Rd, Campbelltown , New South Wales 2560', '', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/xpwxwv1422945136.png', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/logo/vurxuy1422988773.png'),
