(786, 134953, 'Ebay Motors', 2010, 'Motorsport', 'BTCC', '4372', 'Dick Bennetts', '', '', '', 'West Surrey Racing is a UK-based motorsport team run by New Zealander Dick Bennetts. He is responsible for masterminding the careers of such names as Ayrton Senna, Mika HÃ¤kkinen, Jonathan Palmer, Rubens Barrichello, MaurÃ­cio Gugelmin and Eddie Irvine with his involvement in F3 and a racing academy in the 80s and 90s. Founded in 1981, WSR has won more than 70 races in Formula 3 and more than 20 class and outright wins in the BTCC.', '', 'www.ebaymotorshub.co.uk', 'www.facebook.com/ebaymotorsBTCC', 'www.twitter.com/eBayMotorsBTCC', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/xusysv1432775663.png', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/jersey/trxsxq1432775522.png', ''),
