(981, 135144, 'LinkÃ¶pings HC', 1976, 'Ice Hockey', 'Swedish Hockey League', '4419', 'Mike Helber', '', '', '', 'Saab Arena, formerly named Cloetta Center between 2004â€“2014, is an arena in LinkÃ¶ping, Sweden. It opened in 2004 and holds 8,500 people during sport events and 11,500 during concerts. On its opening, it became the new home ice for the ice hockey team LinkÃ¶pings HC, replacing StÃ¥ngebro Ishall.\r\n\r\nThe arena has hosted a Melodifestivalen semi-final three times: in 2005, 2008 and 2011. Some other notable music acts include Deep Purple, Europe, John Fogerty, Toto, W.A.S.P. and Whitesnake.\r\n\r\nCandy manufacturer Cloetta acquired the naming rights prior to the arenas opening and named it Cloetta Center. The name held a double meaning in that "Center" was also one of the companys main brands. On 10 July 2013, Cloetta announced that they wouldnt extend their contracts with the arena after the 2013â€“14 season, which meant the arena would operate under a new name starting in the 2014â€“15 season. On 16 June 2014, Saab and LinkÃ¶pings HC signed an agreement that would rename Cloetta Center to Saab Arena. The change didnt technically take effect before 1 July 2014.', 'LinkÃ¶ping, Sweden', 'www.lhc.eu', 'www.facebook.com/LHCOfficialPage', '', 'instagram.com/LHCHockey', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/rvtwsy1421695463.png', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/jersey/yyyxvr1445083104.png', ''),
(982, 135145, 'LuleÃ¥ HF', 1977, 'Ice Hockey', 'Swedish Hockey League', '4419', 'Peter JidstrÃ¶m', '', '', '', 'Coop Norrbotten Arena is an indoor sporting arena located in LuleÃ¥, Sweden. The seating capacity of the arena is 6,300, and it is the home arena of the LuleÃ¥ HF ice hockey team. Until 2002 it was called Delfinen ("The Dolphin") when it was refurbished and the naming rights were sold to the local division of the Swedish retail company Kooperativa FÃ¶rbundet, who renamed it Coop Arena. In 2009, it was renamed Coop Norrbotten Arena, although its still occasionally referred to as "Coop Arena".', '6300', 'www.luleahockey.se', 'www.facebook.com/LuleaHockey', 'twitter.com/LuleaHockey', 'instagram.com/LuleaHockey', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/qpwpsq1421695844.png', '', ''),
