(1202, 135254, 'Cleveland Indians', 1894, 'Baseball', 'MLB', '4424', '', '', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/stadium/vqvrtw1432312622.jpg', 'Progressive Field is a baseball park located in downtown Cleveland, Ohio. It is the home field of the Cleveland Indians of Major League Baseball, and together with Quicken Loans Arena, is part of the Gateway Sports and Entertainment Complex. It was ranked as Major League Baseballs best ballpark in a 2008 Sports Illustrated fan opinion poll.\r\n\r\nThe ballpark was named Jacobs Field after team owners Richard and David Jacobs, from its inaugural season in 1994 until 2008, when its name was changed to Progressive Field after its naming rights were purchased by locally based Progressive Insurance Company. The ballpark is sometimes referred to as "The Jake," based on its original name.', 'Cleveland, Ohio', 'cleveland.indians.mlb.com/NASApp/mlb/cle/homepage/cle_homepage.jsp', 'www.facebook.com/Indians', 'twitter.com/Indians', 'www.instagram.com/indians', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/badge/rqtusr1432313837.png', '', 'http://www.thesportsdb.com/images/media/team/logo/uwsxqr1432314008.png'),
