(163, 'Terms & Conditions', 'terms-conditions', '', '', '', '', '<h1>TERMS &amp; CONDITIONS</h1>\n\n<p>www.sigod.com&nbsp;promise is simple: to provide online console gamers of all skill levels with the chance to play the best games for the biggest prizes. In order to ensure fair play, and that every member is treated with the respect they deserve, these are the rules of the game.</p>\n\n<p>It is required that players review, accept and agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions and recognize the decisions of the site&#39;s administrators as final, before participating in any game or tournament. These rules spell out the important aspects of eligibility, registration, tax consequences and etc. All rules, regulations, and payoffs contained herein are subject to change and revision by the management without prior written notice.</p>\n\n<p>Player shall periodically review these Terms and Conditions posted at this Web site at a rate not less than once monthly. PLEASE READ THEM IN THEIR ENTIRETY.</p>\n\n<p>THIS AGREEMENT IS BETWEEN YOU AND&nbsp;www.sigod.com</p>\n\n<p>This agreement (the &quot;Agreement&quot; and the &quot;Terms&quot;) is a contract between You (&quot;User,&quot; Users,&quot; &quot;You&quot; and &quot;Your&quot;) and&nbsp;www.sigod.com&nbsp;(&quot;Us&quot;, &quot;We&quot; and &quot;Our) and it governs Your use of the&nbsp;www.sigod.com&nbsp;website located at&nbsp;www.sigod.com, its content, the software and the associated materials made available through this website (collectively, the &quot;Site&quot;).</p>\n\n<p>ELIGIBILITY</p>\n\n<p>In order to register and maintain an account on the Site, an individual must:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>be a natural person, at least 18 years old, and who has had the email address submitted on the account registration form assigned to their use and control as represented;</li>\n<li>be a citizen or resident of a country (&quot;Territory&quot;) where skilled gaming is legal (as applicable from state to state within a given Territory);</li>\n<li>be physically located in a Territory in which participation in the Service you select, or the Site, is unrestricted by applicable laws; and comply with these T&amp;Cs at all times.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Additional Information for U.S. Citizens and Residents: The laws governing contests, tournaments and skilled gaming with entry fees and/or prizes are established by each individual state, not by the federal government. As such,&nbsp;www.sigod.com&nbsp;CANNOT, and therefore DOES NOT, offer fee-based tournaments or games with prizes to residents of the following states:&nbsp;Arizona, Arkansas, Connecticut, Delaware, Florida, Iowa, Louisiana, Maryland, Montana, Nebraska, South Carolina, South Dakota, Tennessee and Vermont. VOID WHERE PROHIBITED OR RESTRICTED BY LAW: If you open an account and/or participate in any tournament or game offered on the Site while located in a prohibited jurisdiction, you will be in violation of the law of such jurisdiction and these T&amp;Cs, and subject to having your account suspended or terminated and all winnings (if any) voided.</p>\n\n<p>INFORMATION REQUIRED</p>\n\n<p>Upon registration and/or during the processing of transferring funds into your account, you are required to provide the following information:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>an alias that will be your username</li>\n<li>a password</li>\n<li>your e-mail address</li>\n<li>birth date</li>\n<li>full name</li>\n<li>permanent residential address</li>\n<li>phone number</li>\n<li>credit card or other payment information</li>\n<li>gender</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The information provided must be true, accurate, current and complete, as requested. You agree to update the registration data to keep it current and accurate. If we determine you are registering with purposely incorrect information, we reserve the right to close your account. Knowingly submitting incomplete or inaccurate information will result in immediate termination of your account and forfeiture of any prizes or winnings to which you may have otherwise been entitled. We also reserve the right, in its sole discretion, to change and/or suspend/terminate offensive usernames.</p>\n\n<p>PROOF OF ELIGIBILITY</p>\n\n<p>We may at any time require any member to provide proof of eligibility to participate in order to continue to allow such member access to the Site and the Services, and each member hereby acknowledges and accepts this condition of their participation as a reasonable measure to ensure the security of the Site. In addition, each member will be required to provide proper identification and proof of eligibility prior to receiving a prize or the processing by us of any withdrawal request. Participants may, at their option, pre-register their identification at any time prior to submitting a withdrawal request. FAILURE TO PROVIDE EVIDENCE OF IDENTIFICATION AND/OR ELIGIBILITY SATISFACTORY TO US, IN ITS SOLE AND ABSOLUTE DISCRETION, SHALL RESULT IN THE SUSPENSION AND/OR TERMINATION OF THE MEMBER&#39;S ACCOUNT. For accounts that are terminated due to non-eligibility, funds previously deposited to the account will be refunded to the account holder.</p>\n\n<p>LIMITATIONS ON PARTICIPATION</p>\n\n<p>You are only permitted to register one active account on the Site. Additionally, we only allow users to have one account per household. We reserve the right to monitor any effort to establish multiple accounts. In the event it is discovered that you have opened more than one account, all accounts will be closed without notice. We reserve the right to deny access to anyone, including, but not limited to, those members who use proxy servers and/or IP addresses residing in certain geographical areas. The Site may impose dollar amount limitations on the transactions in which you engage to fund your activities on the Site. We reserve the right to limit your activity on the site in any way it deems appropriate, in its sole discretion. The Site reserves the right to set expiration dates or other limits on all promotional or bonus funds or credits, including entry-fee bonuses or credits and prize credits applied to your account.</p>\n\n<p>ACCOUNTS FOR INDIVIDUAL USE ONLY</p>\n\n<p>You, as the holder of your account, are solely responsible for all obligations and, assuming compliance with these T&amp;Cs, are entitled to all benefits accruing thereto. You may not allow any other person to access your account, access the Site, accept any winnings, or participate in any tournament using your account information. Your account is not transferable to any other person. All activities undertaken under a member&#39;s account will be deemed to have been done by that member.</p>\n\n<p>SITE SERVICES (the &quot;Service&quot; or &quot;Services&quot;)</p>\n\n<p>www.sigod.com&nbsp;offers its services as a common platform for the users to trace, assemble and trail Skill Contests, and connected information, including but which is not restricted to, Skill Contest Participants, fees, pre-determined prizes and Skill Contest outcomes.</p>\n\n<p>We strongly maintain that we DO NOT provide the Site or its Services for Skill Contests related to sporting, gambling or luck based events. All our services are strictly limited to games and contests of skill.</p>\n\n<p>Posted Skill Contests</p>\n\n<p>Skill Contests can be posted on our website either by us or by users who register with us and maintain a Skill Contest user account. These Posted Skill Contests offer the users a chance to participate in Skill Contest with other users and win a pre-determined prize by paying a small Skill Contest participation fee and a service fee [Together &ldquo;Skill Contest Tournament Fee&rdquo; or &ldquo;Tournament Fee&rdquo;].</p>\n\n<p>User Posted Contests</p>\n\n<p>Any user, who maintains an account with us, may request another user or users to compete in a Skill contest for a pre-determined prize by paying Skill Contest Tournament Fee. The user must maintain enough money in the Skill Contest Accountin order to cover the tournament fee before posting the contest.</p>\n\n<p>Pre-determined Prize</p>\n\n<p>The Prize for such Skill Contest tournament will be the aggregate total of Skill Contest fees given by every participant for participation in the Skill Contest tournament.</p>\n\n<p>Accepting A Posted Skill Challenge (&quot;Accepted Skill Challenge&quot;)</p>\n\n<p>All registered users who have enough money in the Skill Contest Accountto cover the tournament fee may enter any posted Skill Contest by paying the tournament fee. The website will deduct the tournament fee from your Skill Contest Accountafter you enter the contest.</p>\n\n<p>The first user who enters a Skill Contest posted by us or a user who posts such a Skill Contest shall have the right to determine the Skill Contest timeframe which refers to the time limit within which a Skill Contest has to be finished by the participating users.</p>\n\n<p>As long as only one user has entered the Skill Contest, the contest can be terminated anytime without any limitation subject to our discretion. The tournament fee deducted earlier shall be returned to the concerned account within 24 hours.</p>\n\n<p>After entry of two or more participants, any posted Skill Contest converts into an accepted contest which cannot be terminated in general by us but only through mutual agreement of all participants. We reserve the right to deduct the tournament fee from the Skill Contest accounts of all participants right away a contest becomes an accepted contest.</p>\n\n<p>After a posted Skill Contest becomes an accepted Skill Contest, the service fee charged by us becomes non-refundable without any restriction or exception. However, if the participants, through mutual consent and agreement, decide to terminate the contest, the Skill Contest participation fee shall be returned to the original Skill Contest accounts of participants.</p>\n\n<p>Rules Governing Each Accepted Skill Challenge</p>\n\n<p>It shall be the sole obligation of the participants to read, review and understand the rules and guidelines of each Skill Contest and to follow them in their totality without any exception. If the participants or users fails to abide by the latest Skill Contest rules, any Skill Contest posted by them will be automatically forfeited without any exception. We also reserve the absolute right to terminate/suspend/delete your Skill Contest Accountif we ascertain that your actions on the website have been in contrary to our Skill Contest rules and guidelines.</p>\n\n<p>Play Of The Accepted Skill Challenge</p>\n\n<p>An accepted Skill Contest shall be played and completed by the participants in strict adherence with the Skill Contest rules by a time of mutual agreement within the Skill Contest timeframe.</p>\n\n<p>If the participants fail to complete the contest within the stipulated time frame, the accepted Skill Contest will be mechanically terminated with immediate effect and all the Skill Contest participant fee will be refunded to the respective Skill Contest accounts within 24 hours. There shall not be any refund of the service fee charged by us.</p>\n\n<p>Skill challenge results (&quot;Skill Challenge Results&quot;)</p>\n\n<p>The results of the Skill Contest shall be determined in strict adherence with the Skill Contest Rules and guidelines.</p>\n\n<p>These Skill Contest results must be notified with 1 hour of the completion of the Skill Contest timeframe. Any failure to meet this timeframe will automatically result in a termination of accepted Skill Contest without any exception. The Skill Contest participation fee shall be refunded back to the respective Skill Contest accounts while there shall not be any refund of the service fee charged by us.</p>\n\n<p>In accordance to these terms and conditions, a result will be termed as an &ldquo;accepted result&rdquo; and the winner will be termed as &ldquo;accepted winner&rdquo; if all the participants report the same result without any exception. However, even if a single difference or clash or conflict arises in relation with the skill result data, the result shall be termed as a &ldquo;Conflicting Result&rdquo;. We shall try to convert the &ldquo;Conflicting Result&rdquo; into an &ldquo;accepted result&rdquo; in strict adherence with Conflicting Result guidelines. Conflicting results will be tracked, monitored and in public displayed as provided in the terms and conditions.</p>\n\n<p>Rest assured that we verify, analyze and audit all Skill Contest results effectively through an efficient mechanism. Any final decision on the subject shall be our sole discretion.</p>\n\n<p>Conflicting Results</p>\n\n<p>1. No User Reports a Result</p>\n\n<p>If no participant reports the Skill Contest result within 1 hour of completion of the Skill Contest timeframe, the contest will stand automatically terminated. The Skill Contest participation fee will be returned backed to the Skill Contest accounts of the participants while there shall not be any refund of the service fee charged by us.</p>\n\n<p>2. One User Reports a Result</p>\n\n<p>Upon the termination of a 1 hourtime-frame following the finishing of the Skill contest, If only one Skill contest participant has reported the Skill Challenge Result, the accepted Winner will be determined in accord with the single report and the Prize will be awarded to the accepted winner.</p>\n\n<p>3. Users Report Conflicting Results</p>\n\n<p>If there arises any conflict or difference or dispute between the results reported by different users, we reserve the right to solve the dispute or conflict using commercially and logically sound rationales in order to convert the Conflicting Result into an accepted result. The prize shall be awarded accordingly and our decision shall be final.</p>\n\n<p>Our rationales collectively form our proprietary method and at no point of time we shall be required or requested to disclose our methods/approach/system/code/rationale to the participants/users/public. We also reserve the right to terminate or suspend or end the contest or postpone the result indefinitely on our discretion without any limitation.</p>\n\n<p>We reserve the absolute right to postpone, end, and terminate the Skill Contest Accountof any participant who submits a report in conflict with our decision about the accepted winner. We shall give you a one day notice during which you shall conclude your activity on our website and stop using our services. Any time contradictory consequences are reported, we, through our discretionary decision, may attribute such contradictory results to Your Skill Contest Accountand may decide to publicly display the same in Your Skill contest History and on your account.</p>\n\n<p>In some cases, we may not be able to ascertain a winner due to inherent limitations and thus, the accepted Skill Contest will become cancelled accepted Skill Contest. The Skill Contest participation fee will be refunded while there shall not be any refund of the service fee charged by us.</p>\n\n<p>Tracking And Public Display Of Conflicting Results</p>\n\n<p>We reserve the absolute right to record and display all your Conflicting Results publically through your account in order to inform other users about your fairness, credibility and skill integrity. However, if any participant collects over three (3) Conflicting Results in a said&nbsp;THIRTY (30)&nbsp;day period, we reserve the absolute right to suspend or terminate your membership with Sigod.com. Upon incurring any Conflicting Result, You will have&nbsp;TWENTY-FOUR (24)&nbsp;hours to inform us about your reasons, assertions and factual considerations for reporting three Conflicting Results in the said period.</p>\n\n<p>You shall have the right to report to us, any foul play or cheating by any other participant against whom you have previously played.</p>\n\n<p>PAYMENT</p>\n\n<p>The payment to our website shall be made only through our Electronic Payment Processors/ESP&rsquo;s certified by us from time to time. You shall be notified about addition of any new payment gateway on the homepage. You expressly authorize us to instruct and request these ESP&rsquo;s to handle the payments requests and withdrawal requests, if any pertaining to your Skill Contest Account. You also expressly acknowledge that you are bound by the terms and conditions of these ESP&rsquo;s and in case, there arises a case of conflict between our terms and theirs, ours shall prevail without any exception.</p>\n\n<p>All payments shall be made to your Skill Contest Account only through a payment source of which you are the named account holder. We shall not be liable for any unauthorized use of your PayPal or other ESP account. You shall bear the sole responsibility for any action pertaining to your PayPal account.</p>\n\n<p>We reserve the right to terminate/suspend/delete/block your account effectively without any notice if we ascertain that you have been indulging in fraudulent, mischievous and malicious activities pertaining to the payment activities in your account. We also reserve the right to take legal action against any such conduct by any participants.</p>\n\n<p>You can submit a request for withdrawal to us anytime if you wish to withdraw some or the entire amount from your Skill Contest Account. We shall take all necessary steps to solve your request within 1 business day.</p>\n\n<p>Different ESPs charge different amounts for withdrawal requests. Please refer to PayPal&rsquo;swebsite for their withdrawal charges. We may require you to submit certain additional information on your part in order to certify authentic withdrawal requests.</p>\n\n<p>ACKNOWLEDGMENT OF PROPRIETARY RIGHTS</p>\n\n<p>By registering for an account and/or participating in any tournament or game offered on the Site, or using the Services, you acknowledge that all content included in the Services, including all Site design, text, graphics, photos, audio, video, the selection and arrangement thereof, and